Polymorphism in java is the ability of a single entity (method,object,opr)
to take multiple form it helps achieve flexibility and reusability in code base.

1.Types of polymorphism:
   Method overloading (Compile-time Polymorphism)
        When two or more methods in the same class share the same name but differ in p
        parameters (number,type or order) the method to execute is decided at compile time

   Method overriding (Runtime Polymorphism)
        When a subclass provides its own implementation of a method that is already
        defined in its parent class.
        The method to execute is decided at runtime based on the object.